==English==
===Pronunciation===
*līt, /laɪt/, /<tt>laIt</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[lite]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aɪt|Rhymes: -aɪt]]

===Etymology 1===
====Verb====
'''to light''' ('''[[lights]]''', '''[[lit]]''' ''or'' '''[[lighted]]''', '''[[lit]]''' ''or'' '''[[lighted]]''', '''[[lighting]]''')

# to [[start]] a [[fire]]
# to [[illuminate]]

=====Usage note=====
In the UK, as a predicative adjective, ''lighted'' is more usual than ''lit''. So, for example, "a lighted candle" is more usual than "a lit candle".  In the US, '''lit''' is much more common.

